  "prompt": "My girlfriend for 4years cheated 3 times. I found out 2 month ago. She started talking to a guy as a friend. He called her babe, what should I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you're going through this difficult situation. It\u2019s understandable to feel hurt and confused after discovering infidelity. Here are some steps you might consider taking:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Take some time to process your emotions. How do you feel about the relationship and the cheating? What are your thoughts on her actions and the current situation?\n\n2. **Communicate Openly**: If you feel comfortable, have an honest conversation with your girlfriend about what you\u2019ve discovered. Express your feelings and concerns regarding her friendship with this other guy and the impact it has on your relationship.\n\n3. **Set Boundaries**: Discuss what you need moving forward. This could include setting boundaries around friendships with others, especially those that could lead to feelings of betrayal.\n\n4. **Consider Counseling**: Sometimes, talking to a professional can help both of you navigate your feelings and the dynamics of your relationship.\n\n5. **Evaluate the Relationship**: Think about whether you want to continue the relationship. Consider if trust can be rebuilt and if both of you are willing to work on the issues together.\n\n6. **Take Care of Yourself**: Focus on your well-being during this challenging time. Surround yourself with supportive friends and family.\n\nUltimately, the choice on how to move forward is yours. It\u2019s important to prioritize your emotional health and what you truly want.",
